Initially, you are at point (0,0)(0,0)(0,0) and you must go to point (X,Y)(X,Y)(X,Y). At each step, you can either move to the right by 111 unit or move up by 111 unit.

Formally, if you are standing at (x,y)(x,y)(x,y), then you can either move to (x+1,y)(x+1,y)(x+1,y) or to (x,y+1)(x,y+1)(x,y+1).

A path is called safe if there aren't any landmines on that path. Count the number of safe paths which you can take to reach the destination. As the answer can be quite large, output it modulo 109+710^9+7109+7.


